==English==

===Etymology===
From {{qualifier|baseball}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic|baseball}} In [[baseball]], meeting two out of two attempts [[at-bat]]. Specifically, it means the batter has reached [[base]] safely two out of two times.
#: He's '''two for two''' tonight.
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} Successful at both of two efforts.

====Usage notes====
Also used as adverb, but with few verbs.
: He went '''two for two''' in his last two sales pitches.

====Synonyms====
* '''bat one thousand'''
* {{l|en|bat a thousand}}